    "actions_taken": [
      "Pumping operations stopped immediately",
      "Calls made to field Foreman and HSE",
      "Operators from GI 37 R arrived by boat at 1900 hours",
      "Water hose with potable water used to extinguish fire at 2000 hours",
      "Still column to be sent back for thorough cleaning",
      "Perforated plate to be replaced with expanded metal"
    ],
    "summary": "On January 29, 2024 at approximately 1745, a fire occurred on the Glycol Reboiler vent line at Cantium LLC facility South Timbalier Block 23 CC. The facility had shut in due to a Level Safety Low on the Glycol Surge Tank. While operators were pumping glycol into the Surge Vessel, a flame was noticed coming from the Pressure Safety Valve vent line for the Glycol Reboiler when the valve relieved pressure. The fire was extinguished using potable water. Investigation revealed that the packing section was not reinstalled properly in the still column after maintenance in October 2023. Without the packing section, the ability to preheat glycol was removed, allowing entrained gases to be released into the Reboiler, causing the PSV to relieve and ignite.",
    "recommendations": [],
